11,"fifty_day_average":901.1996,"two_hundred_day_avg":912.5652,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":960.74,"all_time_low":770.11,"long_business_summary":"SBI Mutual Fund - SBI-ETF Sensex is an exchange traded fund launched by State Bank of India. The fund is managed by SBI Funds Management Private Limited. It invests in the public equity markets of India. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the stocks of large-cap companies. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of the S&P BSE SENSEX Index, by investing in the stocks of companies as per their weightings in the index. SBI Mutual Fund - SBI-ETF Sensex was formed on February 9, 2013 and is domiciled in India."}}